A 73-year-old man is to appear in court today charged with the murder of his 95-year-old mother at her home.

Police arrested David Powell after the pensioner's body was discovered at her home in Doncaster Lane, Penkhull, Stoke-on-Trent on Thursday night.

Although the body has not yet been formally identified, she is understood to be his mother Celilia Powell.

